			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Soap and detergent are two different cleaning agents. The main difference lies in their chemical makeup. Synthetic detergents usually have a lower pH, making the skin more alkaline, while soap-based cleansers tend to have a higher pH. The first synthetic detergents were produced by the Germans in the World War I period. Today, there are both natural and synthetic detergent options. Soap is the sodium or potassium salt of a long-chain carboxylic acid or glycerol, containing chains of 15 to 18 carbon atoms.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">肥皂和洗涤剂是两种不同的清洁剂。主要区别在于它们的化学构成。合成洗涤剂的 pH 值通常较低，使皮肤呈碱性，而皂基清洁剂的 pH 值往往较高。第一种合成洗涤剂是德国人在第一次世界大战期间生产的。如今，既有天然洗涤剂，也有合成洗涤剂。肥皂是长链羧酸或甘油的钠盐或钾盐，含有 15 到 18 个碳原子链。</common:generalComment>
